description.narrative:
Clean Up Georgia phase III project targeted groups (Local authorities, line Ministries, Communal services, CSOs, local population, media, initiative groups, women, vulnerable groups, etc.) have received significant mechanisms/schemes for further improvement of existing situation on sustainable waste management at national and local level;
Population of Georgia have been mobilized around the waste issue and real cleanup process took place in the country decreasing pollution by 20%.
General public have been prevented from hazard created by HW (chemicals/chlorine); Public awareness has been raised; women benefited from minimization of domestic waste.
The Georgia population 70% has been informed about best practice of waste management, Waste Management Code requirements and Georgia EU Association Agreement statements in the context of waste management sector and habitats assessment;
High level of public awareness on waste management issues and relevant consequences of remaining waste to human health and strengthening capacity of local government representatives conducted.
